I use an old version of Server Express (MS SQL Server 2005 - 9.X) because of legacies issues, therefor I cannot use TLS2 nor TLS. (I know, it&#39;s not recommended).

With R dbi and java alone, the JDBC connection works with this line :
```java
Security.setProperty(&quot;jdk.tls.disabledAlgorithms&quot;, &quot;RC4, DES, MD5withRSA, DH keySize &lt; 1024, EC keySize &lt; 224, 3DES_EDE_CBC, anon, NULL, include jdk.disabled.namedCurves&quot;);
```

For other application that we have (R Shiny, Flask),  we&#39;ve done this replacement in `/etc/ssl/openssl.cnf` and it works.

that
```
  [ssl_sect]
  system_default = system_default_sect
  [system_default_sect]
  CipherString = DEFAULT:@SECLEVEL=2
```

replaced by

```
   ...
   openssl_conf = default_conf
   ...
